  "_documentation": "Roster overlay: who is currently on the EISS board and support team, their organisational role, and their position in the display order. Maintained by the maintainers — separate from form-submitted content (which lives in src/_data/board.json after each sync).\n\nThe sync script (scripts/sync-board.py) reads this file to (a) decide whose submissions to accept (any submission whose email isn't listed here is dropped — board membership is by invitation, not self-signup), and (b) decide each person's organisational role and where they appear on /board.html.\n\nTo add a new board member: add an entry here BEFORE you invite them to the form. Set role to 'Board Member' (or whatever title applies), kind to 'board' or 'support', and pick an order number that places them where you want.\n\nTo remove a member: delete their entry. The next sync will drop them from src/_data/board.json.\n\nEmails MUST be filled in before activating the form — the placeholder addresses below are deliberately set to a non-routable domain so the workflow won't accidentally accept submissions from random Google accounts.",

